/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucaladarremedy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caladar Remedy</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.obenaus.de/germanflag.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#333333>(7/3/02 3:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2770.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GMs and the Everchanging Ruleset</span><hr size=1> Maybe their logs don't work like we expect them to do. Do they really keep track of every single item that drops on each server? Just think about the hundreds of thousands of mobs that get killed each day on a single server, they would have to save the mob's name, when it was killed, what it dropped, who looted what. Now multiply that with a few hundred thousand. Per day. Per server. That are gigabytes of log data per day. Maybe they only log special mobs like Tormax, dragons, epic mobs etc. Who knows..<br>
<br>
However it works, it appears to be broken. 2 examples from recent Remedy history:<br>
<br>
Dinadmera used to have a Warmaster's Ribcage (tunic off RoF boss 5). One day while looting his corpse he went LD. When he came back and had finished looting he noticed that his tunic was missing, it simply disappeared. He petitioned and guess what Vinshayr said (not a direct quote): Sorry, I haven't found any evidence that you have ever had said tunic... Hello? He wore the tunic for 2 months, he wore it when he died, the whole guild would vouch for that. Suddenly it poofs and they tell him the tunic never existed? What kind of BS is that. Either Vinshayr didn't check any logs or the logs simply suck, I suspect the latter.<br>
<br>
Another example: We killed Vindicator and the BP was ninjad. Petitioned and the guide escalated it to the GM. GM told us he checked the logs and no BP dropped, have a nice day. Uh huh, sure. Later that day someone  found out who might have been the ninja looter. We petitioned again, got another GM and gave him the name. The GM checked that person, confirmed he was the ninja looter and returned the BP to us.<br>
<br>
So, that seems to be the new policy regarding ninja looting. You have to know who was the ninja looter else you're out of luck.<br>
