<br>
THE GROUP OF PEOPLE THAT FIRST ENGAGE THE MOB AND HAVE THE NECESSARY &quot;FIREPOWER&quot; TOO KILL SAID MOB ARE THE ONES THAT GET THE LOOT.<br>
<br>
If you engage it, and you have the people to kill it, it's yours. If you send a druid in 30 minutes before everyone else in an attempt to claim the mob by having the druid kite it around, it is NOT yours. If you have one group there, you engage first, the raid with sufficient numbers then jumps on the mob, and your group somehow gets the exp. The kill is NOT yours.<br>
<br>
<br>
Perfeect example of this is Ragefire. You can camp Ragefire for 3 days, and when it finally pops you can kite around the dude that spawns him. If a group of 6 wizards could pop in while you're still gathering troops and owns him, it's their kill. <br>
<br>
If you've got the numbers and are the first two engage the kill is yours. If another group engages first but they lack the numbers the mob can still be considered unengaged and you can take it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bnamelesstavern.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=beardo>beardo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 796<br> <font color=#333333>(7/3/02 11:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstavernrantsandflames.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2770.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: GMs and the Everchanging Ruleset</span><hr size=1> Verant is a bunch of fucken morons, first of all, i agree with muglack. Second of all, GM suck cock, well vinshayr was good.<br>
